    "source": "doi:10.1038/s41592-023-01913-z",
    "sourceFigure": "Ext. Fig. 3e",
    "note": "No 1P excitation/emission spectrum is published for JEDI-3sub; the JEDI3 paper (doi:10.1038/s41592-026-03043-8, Fig. 1c) reports only a 2P excitation spectrum (peak 940 nm) and states that JEDI3 indicators have excitation profiles similar to the parent JEDI-2P. JEDI3 mutations lie in the voltage-sensing domain, not the cpGFP chromophore environment, so the 1P spectrum is effectively identical to JEDI-2P. The displayed 1P custom curve is inherited verbatim from the parent JEDI-2P, which uses the cpGFP curve digitized from the ASAP4 paper (Yang et al., Ext. Fig. 3e); peaks 489 nm (ex) / 511 nm (em).",
